  "body": "<!--üíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé\r\n\r\nHellooo! üòÑ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé-->\r\n\r\n# üöÄ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nAn important feature request from some of our users is the idea of having a \"25th\" word as a password to a BIP-39 mnemonic, which we use to derive HD wallets. \r\n\r\n```\r\nWhat I am referring to is BIP-39 https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0039.mediawiki the section on ‚ÄúFrom mnemonic to seed‚Äù this Improvement Proposal is what all the hardware wallets I'm familiar with use and allow use of the additional word. \r\n\r\nSo without BIP-39 being implemented or at least the portion I'm talking about,  I will have my seed phrase written down and hidden somewhere and if it's ever compromised I could lose everything. \r\n\r\nThis is a very very uncomfortable feeling‚Ä¶ Having only a single source to unlock my keys I may validate with one node just to participate but never hundreds.\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nThe bip39.NewSeed function allows us to specify a password, which currently utilizes an empty passphrase. We can allow for an optional, \"25th\" word when creating an derived wallet for the seed, with good information to stdout for the user.\r\n\r\n",
